    {# Corner-radius ramp. Bare ``rounded`` (Tailwind v3 default = 4px,
       == rounded-md) was banished in favor of explicit ``rounded-md``
       everywhere for grep-ability. ``rounded-xl`` (12px) is shared by
       cards, modal/dialog chrome, and the chrome content surface that
       tucks under the colored titlebar (Chrome.jinja's #content-frame)
       -- the 12px radius matches Electron's ``CONTENT_CORNER_RADIUS``
       so both browser-mode iframe and Electron WebContentsView render
       the same shape. ``rounded-2xl`` (16px) has no active site today;
       it stays on the ramp so future heavier surfaces can reach for it
       without re-deriving the step. #}
